{"title_page": "Can You Stand the Rain", "text_new": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Can You Stand the Rain\n| cover      = Canyoustandtherain.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[New Edition]]\n| album      = [[Heart Break]]\n| released   = December 13, 1988\n| format     = Cassette single, CD single, Vinyl single\n| recorded   = 1988\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]], [[Pop music|pop]], [[Soul music|soul]]\n| length     = 4:57\n| label      = [[MCA Records|MCA]]\n| writer     = James Harris III, Terry Lewis\n| producer   = [[Jimmy Jam & Terry Lewis]]\n| prev_title = [[You're Not My Kind of Girl]]\n| prev_year  = 1988\n| next_title = [[Crucial (song)|Crucial]]\n| next_year  = 1989\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|7flrKMGfwjw|\"Can You Stand the Rain\"}}}}\n}}\n'''\"Can You Stand the Rain\"''' is a ballad by R&B/pop group [[New Edition]]. The song was released on December 13, 1988 by [[MCA Records]] as the third single from their fifth studio album, ''[[Heart Break]]''.\n\n==Overview==\nWritten and produced by [[Jimmy Jam and Terry Lewis]] with [[Johnny Gill]], [[Ralph Tresvant]] and [[Ricky Bell (singer)|Ricky Bell]] on lead vocals and [[Michael Bivins]] with a spoken piece, \"Can You Stand the Rain\" is about a relationship presently going well, but the man is asking the woman if he can count on her to remain by his side, in case things should ever become stormy.\n\n==Release and reception==\t\nDespite \"Can You Stand The Rain\" failing to reach the [[Hot 100 singles chart|Hot 100]] top forty, peaking instead at number 44, it became New Edition's fourth single to top Billboard's [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs|R&B singles chart]].<ref>{{cite book |title= Top R&B/Hip-Hop Singles: 1942-2004|last=Whitburn |first=Joel |year=2004 |publisher=Record Research |page=428}}</ref>\n\n==Official versions==\n# \"Can You Stand the Rain\" (Album Version) - 5:00\n# \"Can You Stand the Rain\" (Under the Lamppost/Quiet Storm Mix) - 4:35\n# \"Can You Stand the Rain\" (Extended Version) - 6:56\n\n==Other versions==\n\"Can You Stand the Rain\" was sampled by New Edition themselves for their 1996 song, \"Home Again\".\n\n\"Can You Stand the Rain\" was covered by [[Boyz II Men]] for their 1997 album, ''[[Evolution (Boyz II Men album)|Evolution]]''.<ref>{{cite book|title=Boyz II Men Still the Hottest Group in Music|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QD0DAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA36&dq=%22Can+You+Stand+the+Rain%22++boyz+ii+men&hl=it&sa=X&ei=xDwIT8q-HoLG-QbU4L3HAQ&ved=0CDAQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=%22Can%20You%20Stand%20the%20Rain%22%20%20boyz%20ii%20men&f=false|publisher=Jet|work= Vol. 88, Num. 13|accessdate=7 January 2012|pages=36\u201338|date=August 7, 1995|via=Google Books}}</ref>\n\nIn 2001, freestyle singers Safire & Cynthia turned the song into a freestyle/club jam, and the song was featured on Safire's CD \"Bringing Back The Groove\".\n\nIn 2003, the song was also covered by [[Guy Sebastian]], the first winner of ''[[Australian Idol]]'', on his debut album, ''[[Just as I Am (Guy Sebastian album)|Just as I am]].''<ref name=\"iTunes\">{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/au/album/just-as-i-am/id270340389|title=Just As I Am by Guy Sebastian|work=iTunes Store (Australia|publisher=Apple |accessdate=6 July 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe song gained attention in ''[[Making the Band]]'', when covered by contestants in the show.\n\nIn 2008, gospel group The Murrills covered the song with alternative lyrics for their album, ''Family Prayer''.\n\n\"Can You Stand the Rain\" was sampled by [[Big Sean]] for his single \"[[My Last]]\" featuring [[Chris Brown (American singer)|Chris Brown]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Trent Fitzgerald|title=Big Sean Says He Didn\u2019t Like \u2018My Last\u2019, At First|url=http://popcrush.com/big-sean-didnt-like-at-last/|publisher=PopCrush|accessdate=January 7, 2012|date=July 5, 2011}}</ref>\n\nIt was featured during the \"Thanksgiving\" episode of the second season of the Netflix series ''[[Master of None]]''.\n\nIt was featured during the [[Lip-synching]] scene in the 2013 holiday film, ''[[The Best Man Holiday]]''\n\nIt was featured in the season 15 of ''[[The Voice (U.S. TV series)|The Voice]]'' performed by contestants DeAndre Nico and Funsho from Team Adam.\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!align=\"left\"|Chart\n!align=\"center\"|Peak <br>position\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|U.S. Billboard Hot 100\n|align=\"center\"|44\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|U.S. Billboard Hot Black Singles\n|align=\"center\"|1\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{New Edition}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Can You Stand The Rain}}\n[[Category:1980s ballads]]\n[[Category:1988 singles]]\n[[Category:New Edition songs]]\n[[Category:Billboard Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Jimmy Jam and Terry Lewis]]\n[[Category:Guy Sebastian songs]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Jimmy Jam and Terry Lewis]]\n[[Category:Contemporary R&B ballads]]\n[[Category:Pop ballads]]\n[[Category:Soul ballads]]\n[[Category:1988 songs]]\n[[Category:MCA Records singles]]\n\n{{1980s-pop-song-stub}}\n{{1980s-R&B-song-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Can You Stand the Rain\n| cover      = Canyoustandtherain.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[New Edition]]\n| album      = [[Heart Break]]\n| released   = December 13, 1988\n| format     = Cassette single, CD single, Vinyl single\n| recorded   = 1988\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]], [[Pop music|pop]], [[Soul music|soul]]\n| length     = 4:57\n| label      = [[MCA Records|MCA]]\n| writer     = James Harris III, Terry Lewis\n| producer   = [[Jimmy Jam & Terry Lewis]]\n| prev_title = [[You're Not My Kind of Girl]]\n| prev_year  = 1988\n| next_title = [[Crucial (song)|Crucial]]\n| next_year  = 1989\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|7flrKMGfwjw|\"Can You Stand the Rain\"}}}}\n}}\n'''\"Can You Stand the Rain\"''' is a ballad by R&B/pop group [[New Edition]]. The song was released on December 13, 1988 by [[MCA Records]] as the third single from their fifth studio album, ''[[Heart Break]]''.\n\n==Overview==\nWritten and produced by [[Jimmy Jam and Terry Lewis]] with [[Johnny Gill]], [[Ralph Tresvant]] and [[Ricky Bell (singer)|Ricky Bell]] on lead vocals and [[Michael Bivins]] with a spoken piece, \"Can You Stand the Rain\" is about a relationship presently going well, but the man is asking the woman if he can count on her to remain by his side, in case things should ever become stormy.\n\n==Release and reception==\t\nDespite \"Can You Stand The Rain\" failing to reach the [[Hot 100 singles chart|Hot 100]] top forty, peaking instead at number 44, it became New Edition's fourth single to top Billboard's [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs|R&B singles chart]].<ref>{{cite book |title= Top R&B/Hip-Hop Singles: 1942-2004|last=Whitburn |first=Joel |year=2004 |publisher=Record Research |page=428}}</ref>\n\n==Official versions==\n# \"Can You Stand the Rain\" (Album Version) - 5:00\n# \"Can You Stand the Rain\" (Under the Lamppost/Quiet Storm Mix) - 4:35\n# \"Can You Stand the Rain\" (Extended Version) - 6:56\n\n==Other versions==\n\"Can You Stand the Rain\" was sampled by New Edition themselves for their 1996 song, \"Home Again\".\n\n\"Can You Stand the Rain\" was covered by [[Boyz II Men]] for their 1997 album, ''[[Evolution (Boyz II Men album)|Evolution]]''.<ref>{{cite book|title=Boyz II Men Still the Hottest Group in Music|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QD0DAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA36&dq=%22Can+You+Stand+the+Rain%22++boyz+ii+men&hl=it&sa=X&ei=xDwIT8q-HoLG-QbU4L3HAQ&ved=0CDAQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=%22Can%20You%20Stand%20the%20Rain%22%20%20boyz%20ii%20men&f=false|publisher=Jet|work= Vol. 88, Num. 13|accessdate=7 January 2012|pages=36\u201338|date=August 7, 1995|via=Google Books}}</ref>\n\nIn 2001, freestyle singers Safire & Cynthia turned the song into a freestyle/club jam, and the song was featured on Safire's CD \"Bringing Back The Groove\".\n\nIn 2003, the song was also covered by [[Guy Sebastian]], the first winner of ''[[Australian Idol]]'', on his debut album, ''[[Just as I Am (Guy Sebastian album)|Just as I am]].''<ref name=\"iTunes\">{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/au/album/just-as-i-am/id270340389|title=Just As I Am by Guy Sebastian|work=iTunes Store (Australia|publisher=Apple |accessdate=6 July 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe song gained attention in ''[[Making the Band]]'', when covered by contestants in the show.\n\nIn 2008, gospel group The Murrills covered the song with alternative lyrics for their album, ''Family Prayer''.\n\n\"Can You Stand the Rain\" was sampled by [[Big Sean]] for his single \"[[My Last]]\" featuring [[Chris Brown (American singer)|Chris Brown]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Trent Fitzgerald|title=Big Sean Says He Didn\u2019t Like \u2018My Last\u2019, At First|url=http://popcrush.com/big-sean-didnt-like-at-last/|publisher=PopCrush|accessdate=January 7, 2012|date=July 5, 2011}}</ref>\n\nIt was featured during the \"Thanksgiving\" episode of the second season of the Netflix series ''[[Master of None]]''.\n\nIt was featured during the [[Lip-synching]] scene in the 2013 holiday film, ''[[The Best Man Holiday]]''\n\nIt was featured in the season 15 of the''[[The Voice (U.S. TV series)|The Voice]]'' performed by contestants DeAndre Nico and Funsho from Team Adam.\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!align=\"left\"|Chart\n!align=\"center\"|Peak <br>position\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|U.S. Billboard Hot 100\n|align=\"center\"|44\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|U.S. Billboard Hot Black Singles\n|align=\"center\"|1\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{New Edition}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Can You Stand The Rain}}\n[[Category:1980s ballads]]\n[[Category:1988 singles]]\n[[Category:New Edition songs]]\n[[Category:Billboard Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Jimmy Jam and Terry Lewis]]\n[[Category:Guy Sebastian songs]]\n[[Category:Song recordings p